 well with spatula. Pour chilli over tortilla chips in baking dish then sprinkle over grated Cheddar. Grill for 3-5 minutes (200°C) until cheese has melted."},{"content":"Serve immediately."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To grate your own Cheddar at the beginning of the recipe, cut cheese in <b>2 cm<b> pieces and grate <b><strong>4-5 sec\/speed 8<\/strong>.<b> Transfer to a bowl and set aside then continue as per recipe.","For your next at-home movie night with the kids, try whipping up a batch of these cheesy nachos. A classic beef chilli bursting with mild Tex-Mex flavours is ladled over crunchy tortilla chips, topped with grated Cheddar then grilled until melted. Serve in bowls with sour cream and enjoy whilst watching a fun family blockbuster."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","40m","6 portions"]}